"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388978","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-07-16","<p>The number of Recorders in post is published by the Judicial Office every year. The report for the number of Recorders in post as at 1 April 2015 will be available on 30 July at:<em> <a href="http://www.judiciary.gov.uk/publications/" target="_blank">www.judiciary.gov.uk/publications/</a>.</em></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>As at:</p></td><td><p>Numbers in post</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 April 2014</p></td><td><p>1126</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 April 2013</p></td><td><p>1196</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 April 2012</p></td><td><p>1155</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 April 2011</p></td><td><p>1020</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 April 2010</p></td><td><p>1233</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The number of recorders who sit in court each year may differ from the number in post.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2015-07-16T15:15:20.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388978/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388978/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388978/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-07-09","Recorders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what estimate he has made of the number of part-time fee-earning recorders who worked in courts in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","6315"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388979","Scotland Office","false","2015-07-14","<p>As I said in my previous answer, I am confident that the Scotland Bill will deliver the Smith Commission agreement in full and will be recognised as doing so. There is no question that the Bill makes very significant transfers of power to the Scottish Parliament in a number of areas and is meeting our commitment to the people of Scotland. It is now for the Scottish Government to tell us how they plan to use the powers which are coming their way.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2015-07-14T11:53:34.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388979/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388979/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388979/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2015-07-09","Smith Commission","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, pursuant to his Answer of 9 July 2015 to Question 5448 on the Smith Commission, for what reasons his Answer did not refer to the independent assessments which were the subject of the Question; and for what reason he has not placed those assessments in the Library.","false","Biography information for Kirsty Blackman","Aberdeen North","Kirsty Blackman","6344"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388980","Scotland Office","false","2015-07-14","<p>I meet with the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions regularly to discuss a wide range of issues. Our changes to working and child tax credits will support our welfare reforms by ensuring that work always pays. Taxpayers should not be asked to subsidise, through the tax credit system, businesses which pay the lowest wages. Instead, we will support people in work through lower taxes and higher wages.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2015-07-14T12:24:16.84Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388980/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388980/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388980/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2015-07-09","Welfare Tax Credits: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions on the potential effect of the tax credit changes announced in the Summer Budget 2015 on Scottish families in receipt of full tax credits.","false","Biography information for Gavin Newlands","Paisley and Renfrewshire North","Gavin Newlands","6400"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388981","Department for Transport","true","2015-07-14","<p>The Department holds the information as set out in the table attached. Not all operators are required to provide such figures.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-07-14T10:41:04.59Z","2015-07-31T10:06:34.227Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388981/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388981/answer","006383 - TOC compensation 09_10-14_15 figures.pdf","006383 - TOC compensation 09_10-14_15 figures.pdf","UIN 6383 - TOC Compensation 09_10-14_15","UIN 6383 - TOC Compensation 09_10-14_15","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388981/answer","Devizes","Devizes","Claire Perry","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388981/answer/previousversion/13907","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388981/answer/previousversion/13907","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388981/answer/previousversion/13907","006383 - TOC compensation 2010-15.pdf","UIN 6383 - TOC Compensation 2010-2015","27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-09","Railways: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what information his Department holds on how much has been paid out by (a) Southern Rail and (b) all train operating companies to passengers for late running and cancellation compensation in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","6383"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388982","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-16","<p>The Airports Commission undertook a considerable amount of work to assess the air quality implications of the three shortlisted expansion schemes. The impact on local air quality and how this affects compliance with EU air quality standards is something the Government will be considering carefully when deciding on additional runway capacity.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-07-16T09:28:21.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388982/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388982/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388982/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-09","Heathrow Airport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of compliance with requirements (a) for sustainable development and (b) in the National Policy Statement for National Networks to give air quality considerations substantial weight of the potential Heathrow airport expansion.","false","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","6347"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388983","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-15","<p>The updated CO<sub>2</sub> banding in first year rates in the new VED system strengthens the incentive to purchase the cleanest cars including hybrid and plug-in vehicles. Hybrid and plug-in vehicles will also continue to be supported by beneficial rates of Company Car Tax.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The premium car supplement will apply to all cars with a list price above £40,000, including zero and low emission vehicles. The supplement applies for the first five years in which the standard rate is paid. Zero-emission cars with a list price below £40,000 will pay no VED for the lifetime of the car.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The new VED system is not expected to have significant effects on the second-hand car market for zero- or low-emission cars. The reformed VED system will apply to cars first registered from 1 April 2017, so cars in the new system are unlikely to enter the second-hand car market in large numbers until the 2020’s.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","6376 ; 6377","2015-07-15T16:35:03.083Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388983/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388983/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388983/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-07-09","Motor Vehicles: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the effect of proposals in the Summer Budget 2015 to reform Vehicle Excise Duty on demand for purchase of hybrid and plug-in vehicles (a) before and (b) after 2017.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","6378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388984","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-15","<p>The updated CO<sub>2</sub> banding in first year rates in the new VED system strengthens the incentive to purchase the cleanest cars including hybrid and plug-in vehicles. Hybrid and plug-in vehicles will also continue to be supported by beneficial rates of Company Car Tax.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The premium car supplement will apply to all cars with a list price above £40,000, including zero and low emission vehicles. The supplement applies for the first five years in which the standard rate is paid. Zero-emission cars with a list price below £40,000 will pay no VED for the lifetime of the car.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The new VED system is not expected to have significant effects on the second-hand car market for zero- or low-emission cars. The reformed VED system will apply to cars first registered from 1 April 2017, so cars in the new system are unlikely to enter the second-hand car market in large numbers until the 2020’s.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","6376 ; 6378","2015-07-15T16:35:02.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388984/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388984/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388984/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-07-09","Motor Vehicles: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether he plans for the Vehicle Excise Duty premium rate proposed in the Summer Budget 2015 to apply to (a) zero and (b) low emission vehicles.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","6377"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388985","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-15","<p>The updated CO<sub>2</sub> banding in first year rates in the new VED system strengthens the incentive to purchase the cleanest cars including hybrid and plug-in vehicles. Hybrid and plug-in vehicles will also continue to be supported by beneficial rates of Company Car Tax.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The premium car supplement will apply to all cars with a list price above £40,000, including zero and low emission vehicles. The supplement applies for the first five years in which the standard rate is paid. Zero-emission cars with a list price below £40,000 will pay no VED for the lifetime of the car.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The new VED system is not expected to have significant effects on the second-hand car market for zero- or low-emission cars. The reformed VED system will apply to cars first registered from 1 April 2017, so cars in the new system are unlikely to enter the second-hand car market in large numbers until the 2020’s.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","6377 ; 6378","2015-07-15T16:35:02.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388985/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388985/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388985/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-07-09","Motor Vehicles: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the effect of the Vehicle Excise Duty proposals in the Summer Budget 2015 on the second hand market for (a) zero and (b) low emission vehicles.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","6376"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388986","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-16","<p>I refer the Hon Member to the answer given by my Right Hon Friend, the Minister for the Cabinet Office on 13 July 2015 (UIN 5893)</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=5983" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=5983</a> .</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-07-16T08:54:49.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388986/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388986/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388986/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-09","Department for Transport: Ministerial Policy Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the name, responsibilities and pay band are of each special adviser in his Department.","false","Biography information for Stuart Blair Donaldson","West Aberdeenshire and Kincardine","Stuart Blair Donaldson","6335"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388987","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-14","<p>After 18 months of work, and following public consultation, I understand that Network Rail has now concluded its East Coast Main Line level crossing closure feasibility study as part of its commitment to delivering a safer, more efficient and reliable railway.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The study has informed preferred options for the closure of all 73 level crossings between Kings Cross and Doncaster and Network Rail has indicated its intention to progress these on a case-by-case basis as part of other planned improvement works on this line.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Network Rail has written to stakeholders explaining the results and its intended next steps.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-07-14T10:26:18.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388987/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388987/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388987/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-09","East Coast Railway Line: Level Crossings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent progress has been made on Network Rail's East Coast Main Line level crossings closure programme.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","6464"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388988","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-14","<p>We are making up to £20m available for a further round of the New Stations Fund and the proposed new stations at Edwinstowe and Ollerton will be eligible to bid for this funding. The Department has not assessed the cost and scope of works to upgrade the line from Shirebrook Junction as this is a matter for the scheme’s promoters. We will be announcing more details on the New Stations Fund shortly.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-07-14T10:31:17.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388988/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388988/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388988/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-09","Railways: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to paragraphs 1.298, 1.307 and 2.31 of the Summer Budget 2015, HC 264, what additional money he plans to make available to the New Stations Fund; and what assessment he has made of the cost and scope of works to upgrade the line from Shirebrook Junction to Edwinstowe and Ollerton so that it can carry passenger traffic.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","6468"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388989","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-14","<p>Transport for the North (TfN) has already received up to £12.5m for development work, £8.5 million of which has been provided by the Department for Transport and up to £4 million of which has been provided from the members of TfN. As the Chancellor announced in the Budget, TfN will receive an additional £10 million of funding in 2015-16 and a further £10 million in each of 2016-17 and 2017-18. Further discussions on funding will be taken in due course.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-07-14T10:34:48.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388989/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388989/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388989/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-09","Transport: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what funding his Department provided to Transport for the North in (a) 2014-15 and (b) 2015-16; and what funding he plans to provide to that organisation in each subsequent financial year to 2019-20.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","6467"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388990","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-14","<p>The Department’s Board met on 4<sup>th</sup> June 2014, 3<sup>rd</sup> September 2014, 20<sup>th</sup> October 2014, 11<sup>th</sup> March 2015 and 3rd June 2015.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-07-14T10:21:33.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388990/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388990/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388990/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-09","Department for Transport: Directors","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, on what dates during the last 12 months his Department's Board has met.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","6453"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388991","Wales Office","false","2015-07-15","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by my Rt hon. Friend the Minister for the Cabinet Office on Monday, 13 July 2015.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2015-07-15T12:17:04.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388991/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388991/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388991/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2015-07-09","Wales Office: Ministerial Policy Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what the name, responsibilities and pay band are of each special adviser in his Department.","false","Biography information for Stuart Blair Donaldson","West Aberdeenshire and Kincardine","Stuart Blair Donaldson","6337"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388992","Women and Equalities","false","2015-07-16","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by my Rt Hon. Friend the Minister for the Cabinet Office to PQ 5983 on 13 July.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2015-07-16T16:25:07.553Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388992/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388992/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388992/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2015-07-09","Government Equalities Office: Ministerial Policy Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, what the name, responsibilities and pay band are of each special adviser in the Government Equalities Office.","false","Biography information for Stuart Blair Donaldson","West Aberdeenshire and Kincardine","Stuart Blair Donaldson","6330"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388993","Women and Equalities","false","2015-07-14","<p>The availability of civil partnership only to same sex couples is compatible with the Convention rights and we note that the application to the European Court of Human Rights challenging the availability of civil partnership only to same sex couples was declared inadmissible on 12 December 2013.</p><p>The Government carried out a review of the operation and future of the Civil Partnership Act 2004 required by The Marriage (Same Sex Couples) Act 2013, which included a full public consultation inviting views on potential changes to civil partnership.</p><p>The Government published a report, following the review, which concluded that the Government would not make any changes.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2015-07-14T16:39:20.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388993/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388993/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388993/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2015-07-09","Civil Partnerships: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, what assessment she has made of the compatibility of civil partnerships being available to only same-sex couples with the Human Rights Act 1998.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","6478"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388994","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-20","<p>This information is not available.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Information about the number of benefitting families and average entitlement in the Preston constituency in the tax year 2013-14 can be found in the publication ‘Personal tax credits: Finalised award statistics – geographical statistics 2013-2014’ here:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/personal-tax-credits-finalised-award-statistics-geographical-statistics-2013-to-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/personal-tax-credits-finalised-award-statistics-geographical-statistics-2013-to-2014</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government is making changes to Child Tax Credit and Universal Credit which will help put welfare spending on a more sustainable path. The Government wants to move from a low wage, high tax, high welfare society to a higher wage, lower tax, lower welfare society. That means more emphasis on support to hardworking families on low incomes by reducing income tax through increases in the personal allowance and increasing wages, than on topping up low wages through tax credits.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-07-20T13:25:53.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388994/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388994/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388994/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-07-09","Welfare Tax Credits: Preston","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many households in Preston constituency he forecasts will be subject to a reduction in tax credits as a result of changes announced in the Summer Budget 2015; and what estimate he has made of the average such reduction per household.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mr Mark Hendrick","6493"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388995","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-16","<p>The information requested is not available.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-16T10:55:44.78Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388995/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388995/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388995/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-09","Social Security Benefits: Ogmore","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people in Ogmore constituency claim benefits that will be subject to the uprating freeze from April 2016 to April 2020; and if he will estimate the average difference between the amount that would be received by a claimant if such benefits continue to increase at current rates and the amount that they will receive under the proposed uprating freeze.","false","Biography information for Huw Irranca-Davies","Ogmore","Huw Irranca-Davies","6415"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388996","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-20","<p /> <p>The information requested on benefit claimants by Parliamentary constituency is not readily available, and to provide it would incur disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>In respect of the information requested for sanctions I refer the hon. Member to the answer given on the 11 December 2014 to Question <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2014-12-05/217571/" target="_blank">UIN 217571</a></p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-20T14:29:07.243Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388996/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388996/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388996/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-09","Income Support: Preston","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many income support claimants in Preston constituency died in 2014; and how many such people were subject to sanctions at the time of death.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mr Mark Hendrick","6492"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388997","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-14","<p /> <p>The information requested is not available. The Department published its strategy for releasing official statistics on Universal Credit (UC) in September 2013. As outlined in the strategy, officials are currently quality assuring data for UC therefore it is not yet possible to give a definitive list of what statistics will be provided in the future. These statistics however will be published in accordance with the relevant protocols in the Code of Practice for official statistics.</p><p> </p><p>The latest official experimental statistics on UC and the Departments release strategy can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/universal-credit-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/universal-credit-statistics</a></p>","Witham","Priti Patel","6363 ; 6463","2015-07-14T16:06:22.59Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388997/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388997/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388997/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-09","Universal Credit: Ogmore","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people in Ogmore constituency are eligible for universal credit; and if he will estimate how many such people will not be eligible for universal credit in 2020 as a result of measures announced in the Summer Budget 2015.","false","Biography information for Huw Irranca-Davies","Ogmore","Huw Irranca-Davies","6417"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388998","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-16","<p /> <p>I refer my hon. Member to the answer I gave on 29 June 2015 to Question <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=3828" target="_blank">UIN3828</a></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-07-16T15:06:08.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388998/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388998/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388998/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-09","State Retirement Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps he took to inform people affected by the acceleration of the increase in the state pension age brought about by the Pensions Act 2011 of that change.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","6414"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388999","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-14","<p>The information requested is not available. The Department published its strategy for releasing official statistics on Universal Credit (UC) in September 2013. As outlined in the strategy, officials are currently quality assuring data for UC therefore it is not yet possible to give a definitive list of what statistics will be provided in the future. These statistics however will be published in accordance with the relevant protocols in the Code of Practice for official statistics.</p><p> </p><p>The latest official experimental statistics on UC and the Departments release strategy can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/universal-credit-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/universal-credit-statistics</a></p>","Witham","Priti Patel","6363 ; 6417","2015-07-14T16:06:22.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388999/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388999/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388999/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-09","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what proportion of universal credit claims were made online in the last 12 months; how many universal claims are pending; and how many universal credit claims are in payment.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","6463"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389000","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-14","<p>I refer my hon. Member to the answer given on the 11 December 2014 to Question <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2014-12-05/217571/" target="_blank">UIN 217571</a></p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-14T15:51:39.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389000/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389000/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389000/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-09","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if his Department will publish statistics on the number of deaths of benefit claimants whose payments have been stopped in (a) England, (b) Cumbria and (c) Copeland constituency in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","6479"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389001","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-14","<p>This information is not available.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Information about the number of benefitting families and average entitlement by region and Parliamentary Constituency in in the tax year 2013-14 can be found in the publication ‘Personal tax credits: Finalised award statistics – geographical statistics 2013-2014’ here:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/personal-tax-credits-finalised-award-statistics-geographical-statistics-2013-to-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/personal-tax-credits-finalised-award-statistics-geographical-statistics-2013-to-2014</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government is making changes to Child Tax Credit and Universal Credit which will help put welfare spending on a more sustainable path. The Government wants to move from a low wage, high tax, high welfare society to a higher wage, lower tax, lower welfare society. That means more emphasis on support to hardworking families on low incomes by reducing income tax through increases in the personal allowance and increasing wages, than on topping up low wages through tax credits.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-07-14T13:35:05.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389001/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389001/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389001/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-07-09","Welfare Tax Credits: Kingston upon Hull","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many households in Hull local authority area does he forecast will (a) no longer receive tax credits and (b) receive less tax credits due to the changes announced in the Summer Budget 2015.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","6466"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389002","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-16","<p /> <p>The vast majority of refusals are either because (i) there was a doubt about whether the claimant would be entitled to the benefit being claimed and, therefore, we could not be sure that there was any benefit to advance or (ii) actual benefit was paid instead, which is a better outcome for the claimant.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-16T11:05:46.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389002/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389002/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389002/answer","Witham","Witham","Priti Patel","Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389002/answer/previousversion/14191","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389002/answer/previousversion/14191","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389002/answer/previousversion/14191",,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-09","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 9 July 2015 to Question 5753, how many applications for Short Term Benefit Advance in 2014 were rejected; and for what reasons such applications were rejected.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","6454"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389003","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-14","<p>The Government will set out its assessment of the impacts of the policies in the Welfare Reform and Work Bill in due course.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","6407 ; 6408","2015-07-14T16:20:12.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389003/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389003/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389003/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-09","Social Security Benefits: Kingston upon Hull","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many households in Hull local authority area he forecasts will be affected by the lowering of the benefits cap.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","6458"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389004","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-16","<p /> <p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by my Rt Hon. Friend the Minister for the Cabinet Office on 13 July 2015 to Question No. <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons&amp;uin=5983" target="_blank">5983</a></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-07-16T16:26:39.55Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389004/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389004/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389004/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-09","Department for Work and Pensions: Ministerial Policy Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the name, responsibilities and pay band are of each special adviser in his Department.","false","Biography information for Stuart Blair Donaldson","West Aberdeenshire and Kincardine","Stuart Blair Donaldson","6338"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389005","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-16","<p /> <p>The Government is committed to continuing to provide financial support for carers, including young carers, through the benefit system.</p><p> </p><p>Councils may also be able to support young carers with accommodation and other costs in setting up home.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-07-16T11:18:52.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389005/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389005/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389005/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-09","Carers: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what support is available for young people who are sole carers for disabled and elderly family members to set up their own home.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","6350"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389006","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-16","<p /> <p>The Health and Safety Executive does not regulate human trafficking and forced labour. If, during their visits to workplaces, HSE’s inspectors suspect that human trafficking or forced labour may be taking place, then they will forward the details to the appropriate enforcement agencies in accordance with the Joint Workplace Protocol for sharing information between HSE and other Government departments and agencies.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-07-16T15:38:23.943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389006/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389006/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389006/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-09","Forced Labour and Human Trafficking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 17 November 2014 to Question 214121, what steps the Health and Safety Executive takes when it discovers evidence of human trafficking and forced labour in the course of its work.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","6342"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389007","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-16","<p /> <p>The level of income at which entitlement to Pension Credit ends is £151.20 for those under 65 years of age and £188.25 for those aged 65 and over (£230.85 and £274.43 respectively for couples). These amounts may be higher for those with caring responsibilities, a severe disability, or certain housing costs. When calculating Pension Credit entitlement, income such as earnings, pensions or income drawdown is taken into account net of any tax liability, and subject in some cases to full or partial disregards. The provisions defining income and its treatment are sections 15 and 16 of the State Pension Credit Act 2002 and regulations 14 to 18 and schedules IV and VI of the State Pension Credit Regulations 2002.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-07-16T16:31:51.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389007/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389007/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389007/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-09","Pension Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the maximum income is which may be received tax free in each week by a person in receipt of the state pension without affecting that person's entitlement to pension credit.","false","Biography information for Liam Byrne","Birmingham, Hodge Hill","Liam Byrne","6346"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389008","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-14","<p /> <p><strong> </strong></p><p>Provisions in the Bill relating to benefit measures will apply to anyone in receipt of those benefits. Entitlement to income-related benefits, Child Benefit and Child Tax Credit depends first on the claimant having a legal right to reside in the UK and then whether that right enables a claimant to access such support.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, persons subject to immigration control (including persons with permission to work in the UK) are generally not entitled to non-contributory benefits, Child Benefit and tax credits.</p><p> </p><p>The reductions in social housing rents will apply to current or future tenants of social housing in England (with some exceptions provided for in clause20 of the Welfare Reform and Work Bill) regardless of citizenship, immigration status, or entitlement to work in the UK.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-14T16:02:10.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389008/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389008/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389008/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-09","Welfare Reform and Work Bill","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, which provisions in the Welfare Reform and Work Bill apply (a) only to British citizens resident in the UK, (b) EU citizens resident in the UK and (c) any person with an entitlement to work in the UK.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","6386"
