"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389011","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-14","<p>This information is not available.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Information about the number of benefitting families and average entitlement in the St Helens North constituency in the tax year 2013-14 can be found in the publication ‘Personal tax credits: Finalised award statistics – geographical statistics 2013-2014’ here:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/personal-tax-credits-finalised-award-statistics-geographical-statistics-2013-to-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/personal-tax-credits-finalised-award-statistics-geographical-statistics-2013-to-2014</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government is making changes to Child Tax Credit and Universal Credit which will help put welfare spending on a more sustainable path. The Government wants to move from a low wage, high tax, high welfare society to a higher wage, lower tax, lower welfare society. That means more emphasis on support to hardworking families on low incomes by reducing income tax through increases in the personal allowance and increasing wages, than on topping up low wages through tax credits.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-07-14T13:38:47.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389011/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389011/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389011/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-07-09","Welfare Tax Credits: St Helens North","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what his estimate is of the number of households in St Helens North constituency affected by the changes to tax credits proposed in the Summer Budget 2015; and what his estimate is of the effect on each such household of those changes.","false","Biography information for Conor McGinn","St Helens North","Conor McGinn","6403"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389012","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-14","<p /> <p>The Government will set out its assessment of the impacts of the policies in the Welfare Reform and Work Bill in due course.</p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-14T16:12:38.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389012/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389012/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389012/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-09","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the effect on single parent employment rates announced in the Summer Budget 2015 to the conditionality applied to universal credit claimants with children aged three or over.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","6404"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389013","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-14","<p /> <p>The Government will set out its assessment of the impacts of the policies in the Welfare Reform and Work Bill in due course.</p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-14T16:28:16.91Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389013/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389013/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389013/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-09","Social Security Benefits: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the effect on levels of (a) child and (b) working age poverty of limiting the child element in tax credits and universal credit to two children.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","6405"
