"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388573","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-07-13","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave the Hon. Member for Greenwich and Woolwich on 6 June 2015 to Question 4832:</p><p><a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-06-30/4832/" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-06-30/4832/</a>.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-07-13T11:45:45.163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388573/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388573/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388573/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-07-08","Renewable Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what recent assessment she has made of progress towards meeting the UK's renewable energy target.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","6181"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388574","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-07-14","<p>The Government is committed to securing an ambitious, legally binding, global deal on climate change at Conference of Parties (COP) 21 to the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change (UNFCCC) in Paris.</p><p>My right hon. Friends the Prime Minister and the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, are actively engaging in preparations for Paris. Alongside other G7 leaders, the Prime Minister called for priority to be given to delivering an ambitious climate package at this year’s COP. The G7 statement included strong language on the need for a deal in Paris, on climate finance and on future ambition. The endorsement by G7 leaders has provided further positive momentum. The Secretary of State has also met her international counterparts to discuss the key issues for the Conference in Paris on several occasions, including at the Petersburg Dialogue in Berlin, at the G7 Climate Ministers meeting and more recently at EU Environment Council.</p><p>There remains a lot of work to do. But my Ministerial colleagues and I will take every opportunity to press for an agreement which includes greenhouse gas reduction targets from all countries that together keep the global goal of limiting global warming to 2 degrees within reach, a regular review of targets and a global long term goal, and a set of rules that ensure transparency and accountability of commitments and allows the world to track progress.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-07-14T13:20:52.42Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388574/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388574/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388574/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-07-08","Climate Change Convention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what preparations her Department is making in advance of the Paris Conference on Climate Change 2015.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","6182"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388575","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-07-13","<p>The Government fully recognises the need for long term certainty on the low carbon transition as this will give businesses and investors confidence, helping to ensure the most cost effective climate action and the development and deployment of new innovation and technology and help to reduce costs for us all and secure growth and jobs.</p><p>This is why my rt. hon. Friend the Prime Minister, along with other G7 Leaders, emphasised at the G7 Summit in June that “deep cuts in global greenhouse gas emissions are required with a decarbonisation of the global economy over the course of this century”, including “striving for a transformation of the energy sectors by 2050”.</p><p>For the UK, our policy on this is already clear and certain, through the legal commitment set out in our Climate Change Act – reducing UK emissions by at least 80% by 2050 compared to 1990 levels. The G7 commitment shows other big economies are also acting alongside us us.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-07-13T16:13:24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388575/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388575/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388575/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-07-08","Fossil Fuels: Pollution","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, if she will make it her policy to support a global goal to phase out pollution from fossil fuels and replace them with 100 per cent clean, safe energy by 2050.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","6162"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388576","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-07-13","<p>The Smart Metering Impact Assessment applies the social discount rate prescribed by HM Treasury’s Green Book, which forms the guidance for central Government in preparing and analysing proposed policies, programmes and projects.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-07-13T11:56:38.873Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388576/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388576/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388576/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-07-08","Energy: Meters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what recent assessment she has made of the accuracy of the discount rate applied by her Department for its evaluation of the total costs and benefits of the smart meters programme.","false","Biography information for Mr David Jones","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones","6199"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388577","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-07-13","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave the hon. Member for South Down on 23 June 2015 to Question 3265:</p><p><a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-06-18/3265/" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-06-18/3265/</a>.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-07-13T14:49:45.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388577/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388577/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388577/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-07-08","Coal Fired Power Stations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, if she will take steps to present a plan committing to phasing out coal burning without carbon capture from power stations by 2023; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","6195"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388578","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-07-17","<p>Support for low carbon development is provided mainly through the Renewable Heat Incentive (RHI) and the Levy Control Framework (LCF).</p><p>The RHI budget for 2015-16 is £430m. Budgets for future years are the subject of the Spending Review.</p><p>Details of the LCF forecast for each year to 2020-21 can be found in table 2.7 of the Fiscal Supplementary Tables, which are located at the following link: <a href="http://budgetresponsibility.org.uk/economic-fiscal-outlook-july-2015/" target="_blank">http://budgetresponsibility.org.uk/economic-fiscal-outlook-july-2015/</a></p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-07-17T14:03:48.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388578/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388578/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388578/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-07-08","Environment Protection: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what direct funding her Department has allocated for projects which deliver low-carbon development in (a) the present financial year and (b) each further financial year until 2020-21.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","6227"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388579","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-07-13","<p>At an official level, DECC has regular contact with DWP, the Health and Safety Executive, the Oil and Gas Authority and Oil and Gas UK on a range of issues relating to the oil and gas industry, including maintenance of offshore infrastructure.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-07-13T11:46:51.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388579/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388579/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388579/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-07-08","Offshore Industry: Industrial Health and Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, with reference to paragraph 3.3.3 of the Oil and Gas UK health and safety report 2014, what discussions she has had with (a) ministerial colleagues in the Department for Work and Pensions, (b) the Health and Safety Executive, (c) the Oil and Gas Authority, (d) trade unions and (e) Oil and Gas UK on the growth of the safety-critical maintenance backlog recorded in that report.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","6156"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388580","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-16","<p /> <p>Operators choose how best to invest in the exploitation of the offshore oil and gas industry. The Health and Safety Executive’s programme of offshore inspections and accident and incident investigations includes both the identification of immediate failures and underlying causes; findings are followed up with the relevant duty holders. Where consistent causes of failure are identified, these are shared with industry to assist operators in directing investment towards securing efficient and safe production.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-07-16T14:09:01.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388580/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388580/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388580/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-08","Offshore Industry: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will investigate the causes of the increase in the backlog of safety critical maintenance work on oil and gas installations in 2014.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","6101"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388581","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-07-13","<p>The energy savings by households and the related carbon emission savings (a) account for approximately 30% of the gross benefits of the smart meter roll-out. Shifting demand to off peak times (b) accounts for approximately 5% of the projected gross benefits of the smart meter roll-out.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-07-13T11:57:05.23Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388581/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388581/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388581/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-07-08","Energy: Meters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what proportion of the net benefit of the smart meters programme forecast by her Department is accounted for by the assumption that households will (a) reduce their gas and electricity consumption and (b) vary the time of day at which gas and electricity are consumed as a result of using smart meters.","false","Biography information for Mr David Jones","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones","6310"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388582","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-07-13","<p>Our central estimate of the energy savings to households set out in the Smart Metering Impact Assessment is a mean of 2% for gas and 2.8% for electricity (both for customers with credit meters). These energy saving assumptions are at the conservative end of the spectrum, based on international evidence. Our modelling in addition takes into account that other policies with consumption reducing effects have been introduced before smart metering.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-07-13T11:56:23.563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388582/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388582/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388582/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-07-08","Energy: Meters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what reduction in the consumption of (a) gas and (b) electricity the median household is required to make in order to achieve her Department's forecast of the net benefit of the smart meters programme.","false","Biography information for Mr David Jones","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones","6311"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388583","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-07-13","<p>The Smart Metering Impact Assessment does not provide a specific estimate of the energy savings that are attributable to the use of an In-Home Display, given that the energy savings households are expected to make from smart meters will be dependent on a number of factors. These include the effectiveness of consumer engagement approaches carried out by energy suppliers before, during and after installation and more broadly by Smart Energy GB, as well as the In-Home Display itself.</p><p>Past GB trials and international experience demonstrate that In-Home Displays are instrumental to energy savings. For example, the findings from the Energy Demand Research Project published in 2011 showed that electricity savings with an In-Home Display were generally 2-4% higher than with a smart meter only.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-07-13T11:54:10.53Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388583/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388583/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388583/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-07-08","Energy: Meters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what proportion of her Department's forecast reduction in household gas and electricity consumption arising as a result of the smart meters programme is attributable to the use of an in-home display for the provision of consumption data.","false","Biography information for Mr David Jones","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones","6312"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388584","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-07-15","<p>We will consider carefully a range of options for the 2016 Basic Payment Scheme using our experience of the implementation of the new approach for 2015.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-07-15T12:07:41.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388584/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388584/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388584/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-07-08","Agriculture: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether applications for the 2016 Basic Payment Scheme will be made online or by paper.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","6112"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388585","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-07-15","<p>Subject to ongoing reconciliation work, as of the 8th July, we received (a) 87,267 BPS Applications prior to the 15th June, and (b) 858 after the 15th June.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>All claims will need to be validated and verified over the next few months and the Rural Payments Agency has said it will be making full payments as early as possible in the payment window, which runs from December 2015 to June 2016.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","6115","2015-07-15T12:09:57.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388585/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388585/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388585/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-07-08","Agriculture: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many Basic Payment Scheme applications made (a) before and (b) after 15 June 2015 will result in payments being received in December 2015.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","6113"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388586","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-07-15","<p>As of the 8th July we have received 88,125 Basic Payments Scheme (BPS) applications. These will need to be validated and verified over the next few months.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-07-15T12:13:52.55Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388586/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388586/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388586/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-07-08","Agriculture: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many applications to the Basic Payment Scheme have been approved to date.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","6114"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388587","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-07-15","<p>Subject to ongoing reconciliation work, as of the 8th July, we received (a) 87,267 BPS Applications prior to the 15th June, and (b) 858 after the 15th June.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>All claims will need to be validated and verified over the next few months and the Rural Payments Agency has said it will be making full payments as early as possible in the payment window, which runs from December 2015 to June 2016.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","6113","2015-07-15T12:09:57.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388587/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388587/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388587/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-07-08","Agriculture: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many applications for the Basic Payment Scheme were received (a) before and (b) after the 15 June 2015 deadline.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","6115"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388588","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-07-15","<p>There are no outstanding requests for assistance with applications. During the application window the Rural Payments Agency offered an unprecedented level of support to farmers and landowners to ensure that they were able to submit their applications.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-07-15T13:22:26.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388588/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388588/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388588/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-07-08","Agriculture: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many requests for assistance with applications to the Basic Payment Scheme are outstanding.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","6116"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388589","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-07-15","<p>The core of the Rural Payments system is working well and we will use lessons learned from the 2015 Basic Payment Scheme to inform our preparations for 2016.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-07-15T11:04:49.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388589/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388589/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388589/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-07-08","Agriculture: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what progress has been made on resolving issues with the online application process for the Basic Payment Scheme.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","6117"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388590","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-07-15","<p>The Rural Payments Agency (RPA) uses a flexible resourcing approach, moving people onto different activities according to business need. Whilst the number of people deployed to processing Basic Payment Scheme applications will change depending on the activities being carried out, current numbers (as at 10 July) are as follows: (a) approximately 200 full time RPA employees (b) approximately 100 part time RPA employees (c) approximately 20 agency temps, and (d) approximately 50 apprentices from the cross-government Operational Delivery Profession.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-07-15T13:31:13.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388590/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388590/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388590/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-07-08","Agriculture: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many (a) full-time staff, (b) part-time staff, (c) agency staff and (d) apprentices the Rural Payments Agency employs to process Basic Payment Scheme applications.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","6118"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388591","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-07-15","<p>Any burbot re-introduction to inland waters in England would be dependent on further research and an assessment of the associated risks and opportunities. Factors resulting in the loss of the burbot from UK waters in the first place would also need considering in order to determine whether they remain relevant, and whether current habitats In England are suitable for the species.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-07-15T13:37:42.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388591/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388591/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388591/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-07-08","Burbot","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if she will take steps to reintroduce the burbot into UK waters.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","6145"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388592","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-07-13","<p>Many plants, flowers and seeds pose a risk to cats and dogs and I am very supportive of measures to increase awareness among the public of the dangers, including through voluntary labelling of products by producers and retailers.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Many animal welfare charities also produce advice for pet owners on the risks and help spread the message of the dangers. Pet owners should consult their vet if they suspect their pet has consumed any dangerous or toxic plant product. Vets have access to the Veterinary Poisons Information Service ( <a href="http://vpisglobal.com/common-poisons/" target="_blank">http://vpisglobal.com/common-poisons/</a> ).</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-07-13T13:20:59.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388592/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388592/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388592/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-07-08","Plants: Labelling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps she is taking to encourage the clearer labelling of plants, flowers and seeds to inform consumers of the potential risk they pose to cats and dogs.","false","Biography information for Jim Dowd","Lewisham West and Penge","Jim Dowd","6172"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388593","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-13","The Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) provides a range of support to bereaved families after the murder of a British National abroad, but does not normally offer financial assistance. We do however provide funding to specialist external partners, Lucie Blackman Trust and Victim Support, who can provide practical support to bereaved families. This help takes many forms, but can include securing financial help.","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge",,"2015-07-13T14:04:48.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388593/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388593/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388593/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-08","British Nationals Abroad: Homicide","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what financial assistance his Department has provided to families of British nationals murdered abroad in (a) terrorist-related and (b) other incidents in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","6147"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388594","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-14","<p>We are working towards a comprehensive agreement with Iran to achieve a breakout timeline of at least one year and ensure that Iran's nuclear programm eis exclusively peaceful. Iran’s use of IR-1 centrifuges is central to its enrichment and, consequently, breakout capability. As agreed in Lausanne on 2 April, Iran’s enrichment capacity will be limited as part of a comprehensive nuclear deal.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2015-07-14T13:16:16.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388594/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388594/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388594/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-08","Iran: Nuclear Power","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment his Department has made on whether Iran's operation of IR-1 centrifuges is in line with that country's claim that its nuclear programme is for peaceful civilian means.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","6187"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388595","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-13","<p>On 8 June, the British Consul General to Jerusalem joined envoys from all 28 EU Member States visiting the Bedouin community at Susiya. The delegation’s visit was to emphasise their continuing support for the community and their opposition to demolitions. On an earlier visit of 10 May, the British Consul General to Jerusalem spoke to the leader of the community about the grave situation and need for the international community to help.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2015-07-13T15:04:16.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388595/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388595/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388595/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-08","West Bank","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what reports he has received from the British consul to Jerusalem on his visit to Susiya in the West Bank on 8 June 2015.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","6212"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388596","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-16","<p>We are aware of a small number of cases where British companies have found it difficult to enforce contracts and secure payment for services provided to state bodies in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC). Whilst legal channels remain the best route for contractors to pursue unpaid bills, and officials at our Embassy in Kinshasa are unable to become involved in private legal matters, officials have recently formally contacted the Ministry of Foreign Affairs in Kinshasa to draw its attention to an individual case with the aim of highlighting our interest in seeing a timely and fair solution to disputes involving British companies</p>","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps",,"2015-07-16T13:40:57.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388596/answer","Biography information for Grant Shapps","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388596/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388596/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-08","Democratic Republic of Congo: Overseas Companies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will make representations to the government of Congo to ensure that UK companies are paid for infrastructure works undertaken in Congo on behalf of the Congelese government.","false","Biography information for Mark Pritchard","The Wrekin","Mark Pritchard","6217"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388597","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-16","<p>The UK is using its international development programme and diplomatic efforts to alleviate poverty and bring about greater political stability in countries of origin and transit. We are working with partners in Europe and Africa to disrupt smuggling networks.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2015-07-16T13:48:59.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388597/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388597/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388597/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-08","Mediterranean Sea: Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what progress his Department has made on tackling the root causes of the refugee situation in the Mediterranean.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre  Brock","6229"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388598","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-13","<p>We support the reforms underway in Bahrain and commend the steps taken by the Bahraini government to implement the recommendations set out in the Bahrain Independent Commission of Inquiry and UN Universal Periodic Review. While progress has been made in a number of areas, we are clear that more needs to be done. The Bahraini Ministry of Interior Ombudsman, National Institute for Human Rights (NIHR) and Prisoners’ and Detainees’ Right Commission (PDRC) have released a number of reports detailing prison conditions in Bahrain and have made important recommendations to the Bahraini authorities. We encourage the Government of Bahrain to move swiftly to implement all their recommendations. We are also providing a range of technical assistance to support the government of Bahrain in its broader reform programme, aimed at strengthening human rights and the rule of law.</p>","Runnymede and Weybridge","Mr Philip Hammond",,"2015-07-13T15:04:59.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388598/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388598/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388598/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-08","Bahrain","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of (a) the human rights situation and (b) prison conditions in Bahrain.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","6255"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388599","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-13","In cases of terrorism, the Statutory Victims of Terrorism Scheme covers both fatal and personal injury applications, and is administered by the Criminal Injuries Compensation Authority (CICA). The latter, reporting to the Ministry of Justice, has received 18 applications related to fatalities since its introduction, on 27 November 2012, and has paid £228,807 across eight successful claims, with seven claims still in process. The Foreign and Commonwealth Office does not provide compensation to the families of British nationals murdered abroad, but does provide advice when there is a relevant local compensation scheme in the country concerned.","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge",,"2015-07-13T14:09:38.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388599/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388599/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388599/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-08","British Nationals Abroad: Homicide","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what compensation the Government has provided to families of British nationals murdered abroad in (a) terrorist-related and (b) non-terrorist-related incidents in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","6256"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388600","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-13","<p>The UK supports a strong bilateral relationship between Afghanistan and Pakistan. The relationship has improved since the election of President Ghani, highlighted by the regular high-level visits between the two counties, as evidenced by the Heads of State visits in November 2014 and May 2015. Cooperation is vital to tackling the security threats in the region, and reducing the scope for terrorist groups to pose a threat to other nations, including the UK. We welcome Pakistan’s efforts to support an Afghan peace process to help bring an end to the long-running conflict in the country. We welcome the recent talks between the Government of Afghanistan and representatives of the Taliban. We will continue to support and encourage close cooperation between Afghanistan and Pakistan. We consider that these efforts can help to further reduce the space for extremist groups to operate in the region.</p><p> </p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2015-07-13T15:11:34.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388600/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388600/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388600/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-08","Afghanistan: Pakistan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent reports he has received on the (a) relationship between Afghanistan and Pakistan and (b) effect of that relationship on counter-extremism efforts in the region.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","6276"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388601","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-13","<p>We assess that demolition of Palestinian structures in the Occupied Palestinian Territories by Israel is harmful to the peace process. Demolitions cause unnecessary suffering to ordinary Palestinians and in all but the most limited circumstances are contrary to international humanitarian law. The UK raises concerns about demolitions and displacement with the Government of Israel on a regular basis and at the highest levels.</p><p>The Government continues to urge the Government of Israel to develop improved mechanisms for zoning, planning and permitting in Area C for the benefit of the Palestinian population, including by facilitating local Palestinian participation in such processes. This year we have allocated £900,000 for technical assistance to support Palestinian villages currently threatened with demolition action to meet the requirements of the Israeli planning system.</p><p> </p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2015-07-13T15:06:11.36Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388601/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388601/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388601/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-08","Israel: Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment his Department has made of the effect on the Middle East peace process of Israel's policy of removing structures in the Occupied Palestinian Territories built without permits.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","6262"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388602","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-07-23","<p>The European Court of Justice's Opinion 2/13 has serious implications for work on the EU’s accession to the European Convention on Human Rights. We remain concerned that accession risks undermining our domestic human rights arrangements and creating legal uncertainty. We will work to mitigate those risks.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2015-07-23T13:15:59.263Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388602/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388602/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388602/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-07-08","European Convention on Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the Government's policy is on EU accession to the European Convention of Human Rights.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","6280"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388603","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-13","<p>We provide technical assistance and support for capacity building and specialised strategic communications to countries affected by extremism, both bilaterally and through multilateral institutions. The UK has also promoted the identification and dissemination of best practice as co-chair of the Counter Violent Extremism Working Group of the Global Counter Terrorism Forum.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2015-07-13T14:48:40.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388603/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388603/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388603/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-08","Radicalism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps the UK has taken to assist other countries in combatting extremism.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","6269"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388604","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-13","<p>Between 1 January and 8 July, there were 234 unlawful incursions into British Gibraltar Territorial Waters (BGTW) by Spanish State vessels. Unlawful incursions are violations of international law by foreign State vessels. The Government does not record the numbers of non-State vessels entering BGTW. They would not, in any event, constitute unlawful incursions.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2015-07-13T14:46:20.933Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388604/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388604/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388604/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-08","Gibraltar","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many illegal incursions there have been into Gibraltarian waters from Spain by (a) official Spanish vessels and (b) civilian and other vessels in 2015 to date.","false","Biography information for Mr Philip Hollobone","Kettering","Mr Philip Hollobone","6277"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388605","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-16","<p>The UN is leading the political process in Yemen to agree a lasting ceasefire and resumption of an inclusive political process in accordance with Security Council resolution 2216. The UK fully supports the efforts of the UN Special Envoy and would support further consultations or negotiations if that is what he recommends.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2015-07-16T14:24:22.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388605/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388605/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388605/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-08","Yemen: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether it is his Department's policy to propose a further round of negotiations between the conflicting parties in Yemen.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","6294"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388606","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-16","<p>We do not have any direct evidence that Yemeni refugees are travelling to Libya and then crossing the Mediterranean.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2015-07-16T14:31:55.853Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388606/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388606/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388606/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-08","Yemen: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether his Department holds evidence of an increased flow of Yemeni refugees travelling to Libya and attempting to cross the Mediterranean since the start of the conflict in that country.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","6295"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388607","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-14","<p>Iran’s stock of near 20% enriched uranium will be an important aspect of a comprehensive nuclear deal we are working hard to agree with Iran. However, it remains Government policy not to comment on the detail of the nuclear negotiations while they are continuing.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2015-07-14T13:28:19.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388607/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388607/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388607/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-08","Iran: Uranium","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether the P5+1 and Iran have discussed Iran's stock of near 20 per cent enriched uranium which is currently in oxide form or in scrap and waste.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","6071"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388608","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-14","<p>On 2 April in Lausanne, the E3+3 and Iran agreed that Iran’s enriched uranium stockpile would be reduced and limited as part of a comprehensive nuclear deal to reassure the international community of the exclusively peaceful nature of Iran’s nuclear programme. However, it remains Government policy not to comment on the detail of the nuclear negotiations while they are continuing.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2015-07-14T13:11:31.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388608/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388608/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388608/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-08","Iran: Uranium","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the implications for his policies of reports that Iran has reneged on an agreement to ship its stock of enriched uranium to Russia.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","6073"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388609","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-16","<p>Our policy on meeting with representatives from the tobacco industry in an official capacity is laid out in the “Guidance for Overseas Posts on support to the Tobacco Industry”. This was drafted in 2013 to ensure that our engagement with the tobacco industry is compatible with our World Health Organisation obligations on tobacco control.</p><p>The guidance is circulated annually to all staff and, in the interests of transparency, is published for viewing at <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/287119/Guidance_for_Overseas_Posts_on_support_to_the_Tobacco_Industry.pdf" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/287119/Guidance_for_Overseas_Posts_on_support_to_the_Tobacco_Industry.pdf</a>.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2015-07-16T14:01:48.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388609/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388609/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388609/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-08","Tobacco","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what his policy is on his Department's officials meeting representatives of the tobacco industry in an official capacity.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","6076"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388610","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-16","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office issued new guidance to all its staff in December 2013 on engaging with the tobacco industry. This guidance was drafted with the Department of Health to ensure that our policy on engagement is consistent with our World Health Organisation obligations on tobacco control.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2015-07-16T14:04:21.463Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388610/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388610/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388610/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-08","Tobacco","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what guidance he has given to staff of his Department on engaging with the tobacco industry.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","6077"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388611","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","true","2015-07-14","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office only captures information about cases that come to our attention, rather than holding definitive information on the total number of UK nationals who are victims of murder and manslaughter overseas.</p><p>The FCO has provided assistance to the following number of cases recorded as murder and manslaughter in each of the last five years:</p><p>2010 <del class="ministerial">46</del><ins class="ministerial">68</ins><br />2011 <del class="ministerial">70</del><ins class="ministerial">78</ins><br />2012 <del class="ministerial">59</del><ins class="ministerial">53</ins><br />2013 <del class="ministerial">76</del><ins class="ministerial">78</ins><br />2014 <del class="ministerial">89</del><ins class="ministerial">84</ins><br />2015 <del class="ministerial">67 (up to and including July 2015)</del><ins class="ministerial">88</ins>.</p><p>In January 2015, the FCO established a new dedicated team to lead on murder and manslaughter cases. These cases have occurred throughout the world in the past five years. Since January, deaths have occurred in Afghanistan, Brazil, Canada, Denmark, Egypt, France, Ghana, India, Kenya, Mexico, New Zealand, Pakistan, Philippines, South Africa, South Sudan, Spain, Switzerland, Thailand, Trinidad &amp; Tobago, Tunisia, USA, and Zambia.</p><p> </p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2015-07-14T15:57:15.6Z","2016-03-16T10:24:42.967Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388611/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388611/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388611/answer","Rochford and Southend East ; Bournemouth East","Rochford and Southend East ; Bournemouth East","James Duddridge ; Mr Tobias Ellwood","James Duddridge ; Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388611/answer/previousversion/13825 ; http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388611/answer/previousversion/14118","Biography information for James Duddridge ; Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388611/answer/previousversion/13825 ; http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388611/answer/previousversion/14118","Biography information for James Duddridge ; Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388611/answer/previousversion/13825 ; http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388611/answer/previousversion/14118"," ; "," ; ","16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-08","British Nationals Abroad: Homicide","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many British nationals were murdered abroad in each year since 2010; and in which countries those deaths took place.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","6146"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388612","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-13","<p>Our Ambassador to Tel Aviv met senior officials from the Israeli National Security Council on 21 June and raised planning issues, including relating to the Bedouin in Area C of the West Bank. In May, our Embassy raised our serious concerns about the potential forcible transfer of the Bedouin in E1 and other parts of Area C and the Israeli Supreme Court’s ruling approving the demolition of the West Bank village Susiya with the Head of COGAT (Israel’s Coordinator of Government Activities in the Territories’), and senior officials from the Israeli National Security Council.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2015-07-13T14:52:29.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388612/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388612/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388612/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-08","Israel: Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will discuss with the Israeli government plans to demolish the Palestinian village of Khirbet Susiya in the West Bank.","false","Biography information for Wes Streeting","Ilford North","Wes Streeting","6133"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388613","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-15","<p>The Govenment does not keep a centralised record of this information, but the information requested regarding voting records of aa Member States on EU legislation is publicly available on the website of the Council of Ministers. These records go back to 1999.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2015-07-15T15:29:06.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388613/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388613/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388613/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-08","EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many times (a) the UK, (b) France and (c) Germany voted against proposed EU legislation in the Council of Ministers that was approved by a qualified majority in each year from 2010 to 2014.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","6095"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388614","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-15","<p>The information requested regarding voting records of Member States on EU legislation is publicly available on the website of the Council of Ministers. These records go back to 1999.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2015-07-15T15:28:42.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388614/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388614/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388614/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-08","EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many pieces of proposed EU legislation were approved by a qualified majority in the EU Council of Ministers despite either the UK, France or Germany voting against that legislation in each year from 2010 to 2014.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","6094"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388615","Department of Health","false","2015-07-16","<p>The information is not available in the format requested.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The National Health Service provides data to the Department annually on the average fee charged per hour for staff parking.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The data provided by NHS organisations in the Northern Commissioning Region for the latest available year, 2013-14, is attached.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>All the data provided has been supplied by the NHS and had not been amended centrally. The accuracy and completeness of the information is the responsibility of the providing organisation.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-07-16T14:43:22.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388615/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388615/answer","Average fee per hour- staff parking at NHS organisations.xlsx","Average fee per hour- staff parking at NHS organisations.xlsx","NHS organisations staff parking fee per hour 13-14","NHS organisations staff parking fee per hour 13-14","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388615/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-08","Hospitals: Parking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how much each NHS Trust in the North West charges staff to park (a) daily, (b) weekly, (c) monthly, (d) quarterly and (e) yearly; and how much was obtained from staff from such charges in each NHS Trust in 2014.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mr Mark Hendrick","6106"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388616","Department of Health","false","2015-07-13","<p>The Department is responsible for determining the price of medicinal products. The Department’s procedures for determining price comply with the requirements of the EU Directive on the transparency of measures regulating the prices of medicinal products. The Biomarin product Vimizim (elosulfase alfa) is currently being evaluated by the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence as part of its Highly Specialised Technologies programme. In the meantime, NHS England has defined a draft commissioning policy for elosulfase alpha for Mucopolysaccharidosis IV Type A on the basis of the clinical evidence of its effectiveness. No final funding decision has been made.</p><p> </p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2015-07-13T16:30:27.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388616/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388616/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388616/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-08","Morquio Syndrome: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the compatibility of NHS England's announcement on 2 July 2015 on a final funding decision on Vimizim with the EU directive on transparency of measures regulating the prices of medicinal products for human use.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","6130"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388617","Department of Health","false","2015-07-16","<p>The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence has advised that it expects to publish the minutes of the Highly Specialised Technologies evaluation meeting held on 17 March 2015 on its website by 17 July 2015.</p><p> </p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2015-07-16T14:09:27.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388617/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388617/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388617/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-08","National Institute for Health and Care Excellence: Meetings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, when he expects NICE to publish the minutes of the Highly Specialised Technologies Evaluation meeting held on 17 March 2015.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","6107"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388618","Department of Health","false","2015-07-16","<p>The Ministry of Defence and UK Departments of Health Partnership Board ensures that the MOD and UK Health Departments work together to meet the requirements of the Armed Forces Covenant and improve the health, healthcare and wellbeing of the United Kingdom Armed Forces community. Delivery of the Covenant's health commitments, including ensuring 'no disadvantage' to the Armed Forces community whilst having regard to the delivery of health services in each of the four countries is a key objective.</p><p> </p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2015-07-16T14:02:36.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388618/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388618/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388618/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-08","Armed Forces Covenant: Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 23 June 2015 to Question 3732, what steps he plans to take to ensure that the Covenant's health commitments are discharged in a fair and equitable manner throughout the UK.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","6139"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388619","Department of Health","false","2015-07-16","<p>NHS England advises that ownership of the former Treaford Lane Clinic property transferred to Birmingham Community Healthcare NHS Trust on 1 April 2013.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>As the sale of this property is a matter for the local National Health Service, the hon. Member may wish to approach the Chief Executive of the Trust for the information requested.</p><p> </p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2015-07-16T14:05:21.103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388619/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388619/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388619/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-08","NHS England: Birmingham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, when NHS England plans to advertise its property on Treaford Lane, Washwood Heath, Birmingham as for sale.","false","Biography information for Liam Byrne","Birmingham, Hodge Hill","Liam Byrne","6140"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388620","Department of Health","false","2015-07-16","<p>Performance statistics can be found on the NHS England website at:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/ae-waiting-times-and-activity/" target="_blank">http://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/ae-waiting-times-and-activity/</a></p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-07-16T13:17:13.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388620/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388620/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388620/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-08","University Hospitals Coventry and Warwickshire NHS Trust: Accident and Emergency Departments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many patients waited longer than four hours to be seen at University Hospitals Coventry and Warwickshire NHS Trust A&E department in the latest period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Colleen Fletcher","Coventry North East","Colleen Fletcher","6068"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388621","Department of Health","false","2015-07-13","<p>NHS England advises that, of the 37 schemes selected for the second wave of Access Fund pilot schemes, one of these is based in Coventry. This scheme involves 64 general practitioner practices in the local area.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In October 2013, the Prime Minister announced a new £50 million Access Fund to help improve access to general practice and stimulate innovative ways of providing primary care services. The first wave of 20 pilots was announced in April 2014.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Further funding of £100 million was announced by the Prime Minister on 30 September 2014 for a second wave of schemes and an additional £25 million has since been added from the £1 billion Infrastructure Fund.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-07-13T15:02:07.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388621/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388621/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388621/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-08","General Practitioners: Coventry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many GP practices in (a) Coventry North East constituency and (b) Coventry have received funding from the GP Access Fund.","false","Biography information for Colleen Fletcher","Coventry North East","Colleen Fletcher","6057"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388622","Department of Health","false","2015-07-13","<p>The NHS Choices website contains lists of all mental health services and can be accessed at:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.nhs.uk/Livewell/MentalHealth/Pages/Mentalhealthhome.aspx" target="_blank">http://www.nhs.uk/Livewell/MentalHealth/Pages/Mentalhealthhome.aspx</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Local clinical commissioning groups commission local mental health services appropriate to the local health needs of their population.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-07-13T14:41:00.363Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388622/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388622/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388622/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-08","Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will place in the Library a list of all mental health services the NHS offers.","false","Biography information for Colleen Fletcher","Coventry North East","Colleen Fletcher","6058"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388623","Department of Health","false","2015-07-13","<p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>Data is not collected in all of the formats requested. The Female Genital Mutilation (FGM) Prevalence Dataset (ISB 1610) began in 2014, and therefore the data provided in the table below is for the period September 2014 to March 2015 inclusive.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Newly identified<sup>1</sup></p></td><td><p>Total number of care contacts<sup>2</sup></p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2"><p>Coventry</p></td><td><p>49</p></td><td><p>623</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2"><p>West Midlands</p></td><td><p>639</p></td><td><p>3,041</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2"><p>England</p></td><td><p>3,963</p></td><td><p>17,875</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em> </em></p><p><em>Notes:</em></p></td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td colspan="4"><p>Collection of the FGM Enhanced Dataset (SCCI2026), including individual patient level data, began in April 2015. Data is being collected by acute trusts, mental health trusts and from general practitioner practices. The first publication of this data will be in September 2015.</p><p><sup> </sup></p><p><sup>1</sup>Patients first identified during the reporting period as having undergone FGM. This will include those diagnosed/identified within the provider within the month.</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="4"><p><sup>2</sup>Total number of care contacts of any type recorded for any patient within the reporting period (NUMBER OF PATIENTS WITH FGM FIRST IDENTIFIED IN REPORTING PERIOD and NUMBER OF PATIENTS WITH FGM ACTIVE CASELOAD)</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="4"> </td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Coventry data is supplied for the following trust:</p><p> </p><p>- University Hospitals Coventry and Warwickshire NHS Trust</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>West Midlands data is supplied for the following trusts:</p><p> </p><p>- Birmingham Children's Hospital NHS Foundation Trust</p><p> </p><p>- Birmingham Women's NHS Foundation Trust</p><p> </p><p>- George Eliot Hospital NHS Trust</p><p> </p><p>- Heart of England NHS Foundation Trust</p><p> </p><p>- Sandwell and West Birmingham Hospitals NHS Trust</p><p> </p><p>- South Warwickshire NHS Foundation Trust</p><p> </p><p>- The Dudley Group NHS Foundation Trust</p><p> </p><p>- The Royal Orthopaedic Hospital NHS Foundation Trust</p><p> </p><p>- The Royal Wolverhampton NHS Trust</p><p> </p><p>- University Hospitals Birmingham NHS Foundation Trust</p><p> </p><p>- University Hospitals Coventry and Warwickshire NHS Trust</p><p> </p><p>- Walsall Healthcare NHS Trust</p><p> </p><p>- Worcestershire Acute Hospitals NHS Trust</p><p> </p><p>- Wye Valley NHS Trust</p><p> </p><p><em> </em></p><p> </p><p>Data is supplied for the number of patients newly identified as having undergone FGM, and for the number of care contacts. An individual seen by more than one trust will be counted more than once, so there is possibility for duplicate counting.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-07-13T14:05:06.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388623/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388623/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388623/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-08","Female Genital Mutilation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many patients treated in (a) Coventry, (b) the West Midlands and (c) England have been suspected to have been subjected to FGM in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Colleen Fletcher","Coventry North East","Colleen Fletcher","6059"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388624","Department of Health","false","2015-07-13","<p>It is for local commissioners, rather than National Health Service trusts of foundation trusts, to determine what services are required locally.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Foundation trusts are required via contracts with local commissioners to provide services, including accident and emergency services. This would not be set out in trust deeds.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-07-13T14:54:25.43Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388624/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388624/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388624/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-08","NHS Foundation Trusts: Accident and Emergency Departments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, which foundation hospital trusts in England are required by their trust deeds to provide accident and emergency services.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","6303"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388625","Department of Health","false","2015-07-13","<p>In March 2013, the Department published statutory guidance to support health and wellbeing boards in undertaking Joint Strategic Needs Assessments (JSNA) and Joint Health and Wellbeing Strategies (JHWS).</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The guidance focuses on the methodology for producing comprehensive and high quality assessments and strategies, and emphasises the importance of understanding and addressing the needs of the whole local population at all stages in the lifecourse, with a particular focus on vulnerable sub-groups and those likely to experience health inequalities.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The guidance does not specifically discuss the inclusion of speech, language and communication needs of the local population in the JSNA. It would not be appropriate for the Department to highlight any particular care group or area of need over another as this would risk undermining the purpose of JSNAs and JHWSs being objective, comprehensive and locally-owned.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>A copy of the guidance is attached.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-07-13T15:01:03.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388625/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388625/answer","Statutory Guidance 2013.pdf","Statutory Guidance 2013.pdf","Statutory Guidance on JSNAs & JHWSs March 2013","Statutory Guidance on JSNAs & JHWSs March 2013","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388625/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-08","Speech and Language Disorders: Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what guidance he has issued to local authorities on including the speech, language and communication needs of their local population in their joint strategic needs assessment.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","6285"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388626","Department of Health","false","2015-07-13","<p>This information is not held centrally.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-07-13T14:42:30.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388626/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388626/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388626/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-08","Accident and Emergency Departments: Working Hours","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, which hospitals in England provide consultant cover 24 hours per day, seven days per week, for accidents and emergencies.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","6279"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388627","Department of Health","false","2015-07-13","<p>This information is not collected centrally.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>We have written to Jane Stichbury, Chair of The Royal Bournemouth and Christchurch Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust informing her of my hon. Friend’s enquiry. She will reply shortly and a copy of the letter will be placed in the Library.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-07-13T14:47:11.55Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388627/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388627/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388627/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-08","Royal Bournemouth Hospital: Accident and Emergency Departments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate his Department has made of the additional annual cost to the Royal Bournemouth and Christchurch Hospitals Trust of providing consultant cover at the Royal Bournemouth Hospital accident and emergency department 24 hours per day, seven days per week.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","6281"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388628","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-16","<p>The WHO guidelines do not refer solely to noise from aviation, but relate to noise levels from any of various sources including other transport sources such as from road, rail, and non-transport sources such as construction, industry and the neighbourhood. It is not possible to have a single objective noise-based measure that is applicable to all sources of noise in all situations because effect levels are likely to be different for different noise sources, different people and at different times.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>As such, the Government has no plans to introduce the World Health Organisation’s (WHO) guidelines for community noise. At a national level, the Government aims to promote good health and a good quality of life through the effective management of noise within the context of Government policy on sustainable development.</p><p> </p><p /> <p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-07-16T09:16:51.28Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388628/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388628/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388628/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-08","Aviation: Noise","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will bring forward proposals to introduce World Health Organisation guideline noise levels in order to safeguard the health of (a) children, (b) the elderly, (c) people with cardiovascular and mental health conditions and (d) other people from aircraft noise.","false","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","6239"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388629","Department of Health","false","2015-07-17","<p>The NHS Diabetes Prevention Programme is making good progress following its public launch and announcement of demonstrator sites in March 2015.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Our demonstrator sites are working to help develop the programme and deliver prevention interventions to those individuals who are at high risk of developing Type 2 diabetes.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-07-17T10:01:03.563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388629/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388629/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388629/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-08","Diabetes: Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what progress has been made on NHS England's National Diabetes Prevention Programme to tackle Type 2 diabetes.","false","Biography information for Mark Pritchard","The Wrekin","Mark Pritchard","6226"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388630","Department of Health","false","2015-07-16","<p>Information on local spending bodies in the city of Birmingham is not centrally held.</p><p> </p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2015-07-16T13:37:46.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388630/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388630/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388630/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-08","Local Government: Birmingham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, which local spending bodies in the city of Birmingham (a) his Department is responsible for and (b) draw on funds voted to his Department.","false","Biography information for Liam Byrne","Birmingham, Hodge Hill","Liam Byrne","6222"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388631","Department of Health","false","2015-07-16","<p>The Care Certificate sets out the fundamental skills, knowledge and behaviours that are required for healthcare assistants and social care support workers to provide safe, effective and compassionate care. It represents best practice and is the benchmark of quality fundamental training. Use of the Care Certificate may be looked for by the Care Quality Commission as evidence that service providers meet statutory requirements for training and induction.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>There are no plans at present to mandate attainment of the Care Certificate by staff, or its use by provider organisations, mandatory, although we will keep this position under review.</p><p> </p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2015-07-16T13:47:17.633Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388631/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388631/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388631/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-08","Social Workers: Qualifications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 23 June 2015 to Question 3195, if he will make it mandatory for care workers to obtain a Care Certificate; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","South Shields","Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","6170"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388632","Department of Health","false","2015-07-13","<p>The Department has not made any national assessment of the effect of hospital car parking charges on specific groups. Decisions on hospital car parking, including charging, are taken locally by National Health Service foundation trusts and NHS trusts.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>On 23 August, 2014, the Department published the <em>NHS patient, visitor and staff car parking principles</em>, which set out a nationally consistent approach for hospitals to take to car parking. This includes guidance on the provision of concessionary parking. The principles are available at:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/nhs-patient-visitor-and-staff-car-parking-principles" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/nhs-patient-visitor-and-staff-car-parking-principles</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>To help NHS organisations deliver the above principles the Department published <em>NHS Car Parking Management: Environment and Sustainability (HTM 07-03)</em> on 25 March 2015. This guidance is available at:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/nhs-car-parking-management-htm-07-03" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/nhs-car-parking-management-htm-07-03</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Both documents make it clear that NHS organisations should work with patients, staff, visitors, local authorities and public transport providers when planning their parking provision.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-07-13T15:04:10.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388632/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388632/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388632/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-08","Hospitals: Parking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the effect of hospital car parking charges on (a) pensioners, (b) carers, (c) people with long-term conditions and (d) people on low incomes; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","6202"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388633","Department of Health","false","2015-07-13","<p>We are advised by NHS England that for 2015/16, around £380 million has been allocated to all clinical commissioning groups (CCGs) to support resilience initiatives. NHS England published details of the CCG allocations for 2015/16 on 19 December 2014.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-07-13T14:43:59.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388633/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388633/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388633/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-08","Accident and Emergency Departments: Weather","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what additional funding has been allocated to clinical commissioning groups to help with pressures in accident and emergency departments in winter 2015-16; and when such funding was first announced.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","6210"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388634","Department of Health","false","2015-07-16","<p>NHS England (NHSE) publishes overall funding allocations for clinical commissioning groups (CCGs). The majority of mental health spending is in CCG allocations and the NHSE planning document for 2015/16 states their expectation that mental health spending will grow in real terms at least as fast as each CCG’s overall allocation in for that financial year. More details can be found on the NHSE website, at:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.england.nhs.uk/tag/allocations/" target="_blank">http://www.england.nhs.uk/tag/allocations/</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Attached is the Allocation Publication letter that NHSE sent to CCG Clinical Leaders, setting out details of CCG allocations for 2015/16, the primary care allocation for 2015/16, the notional split to CCG level to support the primary care co-commissioning agenda, and the indicative specialised commissioning budget by CCG for 2015/16.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-07-16T13:34:02.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388634/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388634/answer","Allocations 2015-16.pdf","Allocations 2015-16.pdf","Allocation Publication letter 2015/16-NHS England","Allocation Publication letter 2015/16-NHS England","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388634/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-08","Mental Health Services: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Oral Answer of the Minister for Community and Social Care of 7 July 2015, Official Report, column 166, when he intends to publish (a) national and (b) each clinical commissioning group's funding allocation for mental health for (i) 2014-15 and 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","6166"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388635","Department of Health","false","2015-07-16","<p>The information is not available in the format requested. Lewisham and Greenwich NHS Trust was formed on 1 October 2013, following dissolution of the former South London Healthcare NHS Trust.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The following table shows numbers of staff joining and leaving Lewisham and Greenwich NHS Trust during each of the two most recent twelve-month periods for which figures are available. The table also shows the joining and leaving rate during each twelve-month period.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Period</p></td><td><p>Staff Leaving</p></td><td><p>Leaving rate</p></td><td><p>Staff Joining</p></td><td><p>Joining rate</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>April 2014-March 2015</p></td><td><p>676</p></td><td><p>12.6%</p></td><td><p>1,051</p></td><td><p>19.5%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>April 2013-March 2014</p></td><td><p>357</p></td><td><p>9.0%</p></td><td><p>n/a</p></td><td><p>n/a</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The following table shows numbers of staff joining and leaving the former Lewisham Hospitals NHS Trust during each of the three most recent twelve-month periods for which figures are available. The table also shows the joining and leaving rate during each twelve-month period.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Period</p></td><td><p>Staff Leaving</p></td><td><p>Leaving rate</p></td><td><p>Staff Joining</p></td><td><p>Joining rate</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>April 2012-March 2013</p></td><td><p>290</p></td><td><p>10.9%</p></td><td><p>535</p></td><td><p>20.1%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>April 2012-March 2013</p></td><td><p>486</p></td><td><p>18.8%</p></td><td><p>386</p></td><td><p>14.9%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>April 2011-March 2012</p></td><td><p>239</p></td><td><p>10.0%</p></td><td><p>724</p></td><td><p>30.3%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><em>Source:</em> Health and Social Care Information Centre, Provisional NHS Hospital and Community Health Service monthly workforce statistics.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><em>Notes: </em></p><p> </p><ol start="1" type="1"><li>Figures show all staff who have joined from outside or left to outside Lewisham and Greenwich NHS Trust and Lewisham Hospitals NHS Trust respectively.</li><li>Turnover data is based on headcount.</li><li>These statistics relate to the contracted positions within English National Health Service organisations and may include those where the person assigned to the position is temporarily absent, for example on maternity leave.</li><li>The leaver/joiner rate is calculated by dividing the number of leavers/joiners by the average of the headcount of staff at the beginning of the period and headcount of staff at the end of the period.</li><li>n/a denotes not available. Due to an amalgamation in October 2013, accurate joiner numbers and rates for 2014 are unavailable.</li></ol><p> </p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2015-07-16T13:59:01.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388635/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388635/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388635/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-08","Lewisham and Greenwich NHS Trust: Labour Turnover","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the staff turnover rate was in Lewisham and Greenwich NHS Trust in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","6179"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388636","Department of Health","false","2015-07-14","<p>My Rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State responded to the hon. Member on 9 July.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Other than the exception of the hon. Member, we are not aware of another incidence of a member not being informed of a visit to their constituency.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","5817 ; 5826","2015-07-14T13:55:55.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388636/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388636/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388636/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-08","Tameside Hospital","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, when he plans to be in a position to apologise to the hon. Member for Ashton-under-Lyne for not notifying the hon. Member of his visit to her constituency.","false","Biography information for Angela Rayner","Ashton-under-Lyne","Angela Rayner","6165"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388637","Department of Health","false","2015-07-13","<p>On 21 February 2015, the Prime Minister launched his new Challenge on Dementia 2020, which builds on the achievements of the Prime Minister’s challenge on dementia 2012-2015. It sets out the vision for dementia care, support, awareness and research to be transformed by 2020, and we are committed to delivering this.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-07-13T14:34:45.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388637/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388637/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388637/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-08","Dementia: Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether he plans to publish a new national dementia strategy in the current Parliament.","false","Biography information for Debbie Abrahams","Oldham East and Saddleworth","Debbie Abrahams","6161"
