"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388731","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-15","<p /> <p><strong> </strong></p><p>The Secretary of State regularly meets with Ministerial colleagues to discuss a range of issues.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-15T14:15:54.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388731/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388731/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388731/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-08","Food Banks: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will discuss levels of food bank use in Scotland with the Secretary of State for Scotland in order to assess the potential relationship between reductions in welfare provision and food bank usage.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","6136"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388732","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-16","<p /> <p>The Minister for Disabled People has held discussions on this matter with the Health and Safety Executive. HSE have begun discussions with the Oil and Gas Authority to ensure its approaches to asset maintenance are coordinated. HSE has raised the issue of asset maintenance at a wide range of industry forums, including the tripartite Step Change in Safety Leadership Team at which both Trades Unions and OGUK are represented.</p><p> </p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-07-16T14:51:49.91Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388732/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388732/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388732/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-08","Offshore Industry: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what discussions he has had with (a) ministerial colleagues in the Department for Energy and Climate Change, (b) the Health and Safety Executive, (c) the Oil and Gas Authority, (d) trade unions and (e) Oil and Gas UK (OGUK) on OGUK's finding in its annual report into the industry's safety performance in the North Sea in 2014 of a growing backlog of safety critical maintenance work on oil and gas installations.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","6100"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388733","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-15","<p /> <p><strong> </strong></p><p>Employment and Support Allowance claimants are usually paid the assessment rate of the benefit while waiting for their assessment. Where appropriate, arrears of Employment and Support allowance will be automatically backdated.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-15T13:33:26.18Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388733/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388733/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388733/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-08","Employment and Support Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the potential effect of delays in employment and support allowance assessments on people who lose their income based benefit waiting for that assessment.","false","Biography information for Conor McGinn","St Helens North","Conor McGinn","6108"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388734","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-16","<p /> <p>There is currently no legal requirement for Dutyholders to report this data to the Health and Safety Executive on a formal basis, this is a voluntary scheme managed by Oil and Gas UK (OGUK). The information being requested was gathered by OGUK and is held by them.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-07-16T15:11:24.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388734/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388734/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388734/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-08","Offshore Industry: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the current backlog of safety critical maintenance work is for each operational oil and gas installation on the UK continental shelf; and if he will place that information in the Library.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","6105"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388735","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-16","<p /> <p>The Health and Safety Executive’s ‘Annual Offshore Statistics and Regulatory Activity Report 2014/15’ is scheduled to be released on 23<sup>rd</sup> September. This will include data on Hydrocarbon Releases.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-07-16T15:13:25.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388735/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388735/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388735/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-08","Offshore Industry: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when he expects the Health and Safety Executive to publish the data required to calculate the combined total of major and significant process Hydrocarbon Releases that occurred on North Sea oil and gas installations in 2014.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","6104"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388736","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-16","<p /> <p>Industry chooses how to invest in offshore oil and gas operations. The Health and Safety Executive seeks to ensure that investment is directed to securing the complementary aims of worker safety and safe sustainable production. I back this approach to supporting growth.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-07-16T15:27:55.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388736/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388736/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388736/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-08","Offshore Industry: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, for what reasons the backlog of (a) planned, (b) corrective and (c) deferred safety-critical maintenance work on oil and gas installations in the North Sea increased over the course of 2014; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","6103"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388737","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-16","<p /> <p>Oil and Gas UK (OGUK) reports that around 70% of the industry currently participates in its voluntary scheme.</p><p> </p><p>The Health and Safety Executive is in active dialogue with OGUK regarding how best industry can track, report and act upon its performance.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-07-16T15:47:59.583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388737/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388737/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388737/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-08","Offshore Industry: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will make an urgent assessment of operator participation rates in the voluntary reporting scheme for safety-critical maintenance work on North Sea oil and gas installations.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","6102"
