"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388745","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-16","<p /> <p>Estimates are due to be published as part of the Summer Budget 2015 expenditure table publication on the 21<sup>st</sup> July 2015, and can be found at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/benefit-expenditure-and-caseload-tables-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/benefit-expenditure-and-caseload-tables-2015</a></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-07-16T11:42:36.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388745/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388745/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388745/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-08","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what comparative estimate he has made of the total annual cost of personal independence payments (PIP) and disability living allowance (DLA) after DLA claimants switched to PIP.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","6082"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388746","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-21","<p /> <p>The information requested on benefit claimants by Parliamentary constituency is not readily available, and to provide it would incur disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>In respect of the information requested for sanctions I refer the hon. Member to the answer given on the 11 December 2014 to Question <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2014-12-05/217571/" target="_blank">UIN 217571</a>.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-21T09:37:51.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388746/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388746/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388746/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-08","Social Security Benefits: Preston","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many claimants of (a) employment and support allowance and (b) jobseeker's allowance in Preston constituency died in 2014; and how many such claimants were on sanctions at the time of their death.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mr Mark Hendrick","6288"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388747","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-13","<p /> <p>It is the Department’s policy to make as wide a range of detailed statistics available via on-line tools to allow everyone equality of access and support the Government’s Open Data agenda. These are designed to be comprehensive and easy to use so all users can extract the information they need. DWP staff will be holding training sessions for the House of Commons officials and MP’s in the near future.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-07-13T16:35:58.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388747/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388747/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388747/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-08","Social Security Benefits: Aberdeen","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 17 June 2015 to Question 3935, what factors in addition to efficiency his Department took into account in its decision to use links to Stat-Xplore to answer Parliamentary Questions.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","6257"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388748","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-07-13","<p>The Low Pay Commission (LPC) is an independent body that advises the Government about the National Minimum Wage, including the rate for 16-17 year olds. The LPC recommended that from October 2015 the 16-17 year old rate would be £3.87 an (increase of 2.2%). The LPC’s recommendations follow consultation with businesses and workers and their representatives, together with extensive research and analysis. The LPC’s report can be found at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/national-minimum-wage-low-pay-commission-report-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/national-minimum-wage-low-pay-commission-report-2015</a>. Having considered the LPC’s report, the Government accepted its recommendation and laid draft uprating regulations in Parliament on 23 June 2015.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2015-07-13T09:23:02.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388748/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388748/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388748/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-07-08","Minimum Wage: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment his Department has made of the adequacy of the minimum wage for people aged under 18; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","6271"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388749","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-13","<p>This Government is committed to working to eliminate child poverty and improving life chances for children.</p><p> </p><p>We have recently outlined a new approach to tackle the root causes of poverty and make a real difference to children’s lives. The Welfare Reform and Work Bill, introduced to Parliament on 9 July, includes a new statutory duty for Government to report on measures of worklessness and educational attainment. This will drive action that makes the biggest difference to the lives of poor children, both now and in the future.</p><p> </p><p>We will set our further plans in a Life Chances Strategy in due course.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-13T13:55:57.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388749/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388749/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388749/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-08","Children: Poverty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps his Department is taking to reduce the prevalence of child poverty; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","6272"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388750","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-13","<p>By working with contractors, we have ensured all staff in London are paid the Living Wage. We are currently I discussions aimed at ensuring the same is true in all sites across the country.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-13T13:51:08.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388750/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388750/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388750/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-08","Department for Work and Pensions: Living Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 8 July 2015 to Question 5553, how many of the outsourced staff working for his Department's contractors and their service partners outside London who are paid at or below the Living Wage are paid (a) the Living Wage and (b) less than the Living Wage.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","6284"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388751","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-16","<p /> <p>Under the Social Security (Notification of Deaths) Regulations 2012 and s125 of Social Security Administration Act 1992 date of death is provided to the Department for all registered deaths. Additionally next of kin also provide information on the date of death of an individual. This information is not routinely compiled or published.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-07-16T15:55:37.53Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388751/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388751/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388751/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-08","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what statistical information his Department holds on deaths of (a) all benefit claimants, (b) all such claimants after losing their entitlement and (c) claimants who had lost their entitlement to disability living allowance.","false","Biography information for Dawn Butler","Brent Central","Dawn Butler","6224"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388752","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-16","<p /> <p>No such assessment has been made. My Rt. Hon. Friend the Chancellor of the Exchequer, made clear in his summer budget on 8 July that the Government has no plans to tax or means-test disability benefits [Official Report, column 333].</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-07-16T16:16:48.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388752/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388752/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388752/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-08","Social Security Benefits: Multiple Sclerosis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment the Government has made of the effect of taxing or means-testing of disability living allowance and personal independence payment claims on people with multiple sclerosis.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","6190"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388753","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-15","<p /> <p /> <p /> <p>The information requested could only be provided at a disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-07-15T13:28:42.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388753/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388753/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388753/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-08","Personal Independence Payment: Multiple Sclerosis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people with multiple sclerosis have had their personal independence payment award reviewed before the end of the award; and how many such people have had more than one review of their award.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","6189"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388754","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-13","<p /> <p>Following agreement from the Ministers in the Department at the time, the internal guidance for answering Parliamentary Questions that contain official statistics was updated in 2012. It is not departmental policy to place internal guidance in the House of Commons library.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-07-13T16:22:28.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388754/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388754/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388754/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-08","Social Security Benefits: Aberdeen","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 2 July 2015 to Question 3935, what the agreed procedures referred to are; when and by whom they were agreed; and if he will place in the Library a copy of those procedures.","false","Biography information for Kirsty Blackman","Aberdeen North","Kirsty Blackman","6306"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389062","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-15","<p>The safety of British nationals is our overriding priority. This Government has set out a clear strategy to tackle terrorism at home and abroad. We will continue to work with our partners and in countries where terrorist groups operate in order to prevent attacks. We will continue to produce objective travel advice based upon the latest Joint Terrorism Assessment Centre security assessments to allow British people to make informed decisions about travel.</p>","Runnymede and Weybridge","Mr Philip Hammond",,"2015-07-15T14:34:56.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389062/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389062/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389062/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-08","Terrorism: British Nationals Abroad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps his Department is taking to ensure the safety from terrorism of UK citizens on holiday overseas.","false","Biography information for Johnny Mercer","Plymouth, Moor View","Johnny Mercer","900993"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389603","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-14","<p>The UK is leading the way through alleviating poverty and working to stabilise countries of origin and transit. We are disrupting smuggling networks. We are tackling the perception that getting on a boat will lead to automatic entry into the EU and we continue to work closely with EU and African partners.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2015-07-14T14:29:24.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389603/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389603/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389603/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-08","Mediterranean Sea: Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps his Department is taking to address the root causes of the refugee situation in the Mediterranean.","false","Biography information for Jo Churchill","Bury St Edmunds","Jo Churchill","901008"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389604","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-14","<p>The Prime Minister, my right hon. Friend the Member for Witney (Mr Cameron), the Chancellor of the Exchequer, my right hon. Friend the Member for Tatton (Mr Osborne), the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my right hon. Friend the Member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Mr Hammond) and I are focussed on successfully reforming and renegotiating our relationship with the EU. The June European Council saw the successful launch of a process of technical discussions on EU reform. Leaders have agreed to return to the issue at the December European Council.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2015-07-14T14:31:19.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389604/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389604/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389604/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-08","European Union","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the progress of negotiations to reform (a) the EU and (b) the UK's relationship with the EU.","false","Biography information for Mr Marcus Fysh","Yeovil","Marcus Fysh","901013"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389605","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-14","<p>The Prime Minister, my right hon. Friend the Member for Witney (Mr Cameron), the Chancellor of the Exchequer, my right hon. Friend the Member for Tatton (Mr Osborne), the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my right hon. Friend the Member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Mr Hammond) and I are focussed on successfully reforming and renegotiating our relationship with the EU. The June European Council saw the successful launch of a process of technical discussions on EU reform. Leaders have agreed to return to the issue at the December European Council.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2015-07-14T14:30:44.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389605/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389605/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389605/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-08","European Union","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the progress of negotiations to reform (a) the EU and (b) the UK's relationship with the EU.","false","Biography information for Steve Double","St Austell and Newquay","Steve Double","901010"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389606","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-14","<p>The Joint Terrorism Analysis Centre continually monitors the international terrorist threat to the UK and our interests overseas. Foreign and Commonwealth Office travel advice draws on their assessments, together with other sources of information, to help the British public to make informed decisions about travel.</p><p>The murder of 38 innocent holiday-makers on 26 June was a stark and dreadful illustration that the threat across much of north Africa is high.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2015-07-14T14:03:36.493Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389606/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389606/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/389606/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-08","North Africa: Terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the level of the terrorist threat to UK nationals in North Africa.","false","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr   Poulter","901014"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388018","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-07-21","<p /> <p>The Data Protection Act 1998 requires every data controller who is processing personal information to register with the Information Commissioner’s Office (ICO) unless they are exempt. Failure to do so is a criminal offence.</p><p>The ICO’s website sets out the criteria for notification and provides guidance on the level of fee organisations should be paying. The ICO have also made it easier for organisations to notify and pay the fee by introducing online payments.</p><p>In 2014/15 the ICO brought eight prosecutions against organisations for non-notification and two prosecutions for wrong purposes.</p><p>The Ministry of Justice and the ICO are looking at the current funding model as part of negotiations on the proposed EU Data Protection Regulation.</p>",,"Lord Faulks","HL1146 ; HL1147","2015-07-21T13:14:42.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388018/answer","Biography information for Lord Faulks","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388018/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388018/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-07-07","Data Protection","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what steps have been taken and what steps they plan to take to increase the number of registrations with the Information Commissioner’s Office; what estimate they have made of the consequential annual increase in income, and of the recovery of lost income from those who have not paid the required fee as data controllers; and what assessment they have made of current levels of fees.","false","Biography information for Lord Alton of Liverpool",,"Lord Alton of Liverpool","HL1144"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388019","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-07-21","<p>The Information Commissioner’s Office’s (ICO) data protection activities are funded by fees from organisations that process personal data. The amount available to spend each year is dependent on the number of organisations that notify with the ICO.</p>",,"Lord Faulks",,"2015-07-21T14:02:00.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388019/answer","Biography information for Lord Faulks","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388019/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388019/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-07-07","Data Protection","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what budgetary provision the Information Commissioner’s Office has made regarding its data protection activities for the next financial year.","false","Biography information for Lord Alton of Liverpool",,"Lord Alton of Liverpool","HL1145"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388020","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-07-21","<p>The Data Protection Act 1998 requires every data controller who is processing personal information to register with the Information Commissioner’s Office (ICO) unless they are exempt. Failure to do so is a criminal offence.</p><p>The ICO’s website sets out the criteria for notification and provides guidance on the level of fee organisations should be paying. The ICO have also made it easier for organisations to notify and pay the fee by introducing online payments.</p><p>In 2014/15 the ICO brought eight prosecutions against organisations for non-notification and two prosecutions for wrong purposes.</p><p>The Ministry of Justice and the ICO are looking at the current funding model as part of negotiations on the proposed EU Data Protection Regulation.</p>",,"Lord Faulks","HL1144 ; HL1147","2015-07-21T13:14:42.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388020/answer","Biography information for Lord Faulks","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388020/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388020/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-07-07","Data Protection","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the financial incentive or disincentive for the Information Commissioner’s Office to maximise the registration fee income it receives and recoup any registration fee income that has not been paid by data controllers in previous years.","false","Biography information for Lord Alton of Liverpool",,"Lord Alton of Liverpool","HL1146"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388021","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-07-21","<p>The Data Protection Act 1998 requires every data controller who is processing personal information to register with the Information Commissioner’s Office (ICO) unless they are exempt. Failure to do so is a criminal offence.</p><p>The ICO’s website sets out the criteria for notification and provides guidance on the level of fee organisations should be paying. The ICO have also made it easier for organisations to notify and pay the fee by introducing online payments.</p><p>In 2014/15 the ICO brought eight prosecutions against organisations for non-notification and two prosecutions for wrong purposes.</p><p>The Ministry of Justice and the ICO are looking at the current funding model as part of negotiations on the proposed EU Data Protection Regulation.</p>",,"Lord Faulks","HL1144 ; HL1146","2015-07-21T13:14:42.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388021/answer","Biography information for Lord Faulks","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388021/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/388021/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-07-07","Data Protection","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what consideration the Information Commissioner’s Office and the Ministry of Justice have given to ensuring that action is taken against all those who have not complied with their registration obligations; what weight the possible disadvantage to those who have paid their due fees is given in deciding whether to prosecute non-registration; and what assessment they have made of whether all those involved in the administration of justice are compliant.","false","Biography information for Lord Alton of Liverpool",,"Lord Alton of Liverpool","HL1147"
